<h2>International User Research</h2>
<p>The next book I read in this collection was <strong><a href="http://www.fivesimplesteps.com/products/international-user-research" target="_blank">International User Research</a></strong> by Chui Chui Tan.</p>
<p>Now I must admit that when I first saw this book I wasn't sure how it would apply to me and my current work. However I decided to give it a try as in the past I've found with a lot of these awesome Five Simple Steps books I've often thought that and be amazed by how they turned out.</p>

<blockquote class="pullquote">The methods detailed later on in the book would definitely prove valuable to anyone undertaking this type of research.</blockquote>

<p>Throughout this pocket guide I learned a lot about website usage in a variety of countries all around the world and it was very interesting, especially learning how Asian culture and values impacts usage. The author shows some examples of Chinese taxi service mobile apps which I thought were really intriguing - they've really got it right over there.</p>
<p>Chui Chui Tan then goes on to banish some myths about how Asian users interact with websites and why - also providing a link to a detailed presentation on the subject which I again had to skip out of the book for a while to read!</p>
<p>The methods detailed later on in the book would definitely prove valuable to anyone undertaking this type of research and really made me want a chance to do something like this. Unfortunately at present I don't have this opportunity but still enjoyed reading through the advice and resources given.</p>

